A former President Goodluck Jonathan's cousin, Mike Ogiasa, who was abducted by gunmen in Bayelsa State, has cried for his life in the kidnapper’s den in a video which has now gone viral.Ogiasa, an Engineer was kidnapped on June 4, 2022 in his hometown of Otuabadi in Ogbia Local Government Area. The victim, who was a Special Adviser on Power Development during the administration of former Governor Seriake Dickson, is also the Convener of a socio-political group, Voice of the South-South (VSS).In the 27 seconds video which SaharaReporters obtained, Ogiasa is seen half-naked in a flooded grave.His hands were tied, as he cries out for urgent help.  WATCH: Kidnappers Release Disturbing Video Of Abducted Former Nigerian President, @GEJonathanâs Cousin Mike Ogiasa Crying For Help Inside A shallow GraveFULL VIDEO: https://t.co/sXmTAe4zyZ pic.twitter.com/It9o8IKhtk 